description:
Add --watch flag to ticker that idles when no tasks available instead of exiting:

```bash
ticker run --auto --watch              # Watch indefinitely
ticker run --auto --watch --timeout 1h # Watch with timeout
ticker run --auto --watch --poll 5s    # Custom poll interval
```

Implementation:
```go
func (e *Engine) RunWatch(epicID string, timeout, pollInterval time.Duration) error {
    deadline := time.Now().Add(timeout)

    for {
        // Check timeout
        if timeout > 0 && time.Now().After(deadline) {
            return nil
        }

        // Try to get next task
        task, err := e.ticks.NextTask(epicID)
        if err != nil {
            return err
        }

        if task != nil {
            // Process task
            if err := e.processTask(task); err != nil {
                return err
            }
            continue
        }

        // No tasks - enter idle state
        e.callbacks.OnIdle()

        // Poll for changes
        select {
        case <-time.After(pollInterval):
            continue
        case <-e.quit:
            return nil
        }
    }
}
```

Acceptance criteria:
- [ ] --watch flag enables watch mode
- [ ] Engine idles when no tasks available
- [ ] Polls at configurable interval (default 10s)
- [ ] Resumes when tasks become available
- [ ] --timeout limits watch duration
- [ ] Graceful shutdown on quit signal
